Any idea how to make it faster? Thx?

data %<>%
group_by(loc, time, agent1, agent2) %>%
summarise(
 across(starts_with("action_"), sum), 
 across(c(feat1, feat2, ...), mean)
 across(starts_with(c("ctry", "cit")), first)
)

Setup: 3 mill obs. 100 vars. Task: aggregation. 
Before: group_by() + summarize=() + across()

Intervention: https://t.co/QEm4l1qKkj +via @JagersbergKnut 

After: dat2=data.table(dat) + summarise.() + by.() + across.()
